cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DC 

This paper deals with privacy challenges in IoT applications, specifically authentication, authorization, and confidentiality of personal data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses managing user profiles, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The implementation of the solution involves the evolution of middleware, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
